ional Red Cross and Red Crescent</a> (1963)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Martin_Luther_King,_Jr." title="Martin Luther King, Jr.">Martin Luther King, Jr.</a> (1964)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/United_Nations_Children%27s_Fund" title="United Nations Children's Fund">UNICEF</a> (1965)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Ren%C3%A9_Cassin" title="René Cassin">René Cassin</a> (1968)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/International_Labour_Organization" title="International Labour Organization">International Labour Organization</a> (1969)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Norman_Borlaug" title="Norman Borlaug">Norman Borlaug</a> (1970)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Willy_Brandt" title="Willy Brandt">Willy Brandt</a> (1971)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Henry_Kissinger" title="Henry Kissinger">Henry Kissinger</a> / <i><a href="/wiki/Le_Duc_Tho" title="Le Duc Tho">Le Duc Tho</a> (declined award)</i> (1973)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Se%C3%A1n_MacBride" title="Seán MacBride">Seán MacBride</a> / <a href="/wiki/Eisaku_Sat%C5%8D" title="Eisaku Satō">Eisaku Satō</a> (1974)<span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span></span> <span style="white-space:nowrap;"><strong class="selflink">Andrei Sakharov</strong> (1975)</span></p>
